Definition: Patient. Sections A1.1 of the eHN guideline.
The family name/surname/last name of the patient. This field can contain more than one element or multiple fields could be present.

The given name/first name of the patient (also known as forename or first 
name) [ISO TS 22220:2011]. This field can contain more than one element.

The date of birth of the patient [ISO TS 22220:2011].
This field may contain only the year if the day and month are not available, 
e.g.: 2009 - Preferred system(s): ISO 8601
Country ID, unique to the patient in that country. Example: ID for a Portuguese patient, national healthcare patient ID. Multiple identifiers could be provided.

This field must contain a recognised valid value for 'administrative gender'. 
If different, 'physiological sex' should be communicated elsewhere.
The native language of the patient. This may be important for the information that is given to the patient regarding use of the prescribed product [N1228 ISO NP TS 17251]
